attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is an IoT botnet client, likely a Mirai variant. It possesses worm-like propagation capabilities through a Telnet brute-forcing module (function `sub_410b2c`) which contains a large list of hardcoded default credentials (e.g., `root`/`vizxv`, `admin`/`admin`). The binary also includes a downloader function (`sub_410724`) that constructs an HTTP request (`GET /dlr.`) to fetch and execute secondary payloads. Additionally, it performs extensive process enumeration via the `/proc` filesystem to gather information and likely terminate competing processes.
